L1 & L2 are misleading names. They aren't blockchain "layers". They refer to replication.

L1 = databases replicated by multiple parties through a consensus protocol.

L2 = databases replicated by single parties.

L1 & L2 are misleading names. They aren't blockchain "layers". They refer to replication.

L1 = databases replicated by multiple parties through a consensus protocol.

L2 = databases replicated by single parties.

E.g. w/e L2 Uniswap V3 runs on will be centralized.

L1 & L2 are misleading names. They aren't blockchain "layers". They refer to replication.

L1 = databases replicated by multiple parties through a consensus protocol.

L2 = databases replicated by single parties.

E.g. w/e L2 Uniswap V3 runs on will be centralized.

L1 & L2 are misleading names. They aren't blockchain "layers". They refer to replication.

L1 = databases replicated by multiple parties through a consensus protocol.

L2 = databases replicated by single parties.

L1 & L2 are misleading names. They aren't blockchain "layers". They refer to replication.

L1 = databases replicated by multiple parties through a consensus protocol.

L2 = databases replicated by single parties.

E.g. w/e L2 Uniswap V3 runs on will be centralized.

L1 & L2 are misleading names. They aren't blockchain "layers". They refer to replication.

L1 = databases replicated by multiple parties through a consensus protocol.

L2 = databases replicated by single parties.

E.g. w/e L2 Uniswap V3 runs on will be centralized.

L1 & L2 are misleading names. They aren't blockchain "layers". They refer to replication.

L1 = databases replicated by multiple parties through a consensus protocol.

L2 = databases replicated by single parties.

L1 & L2 are misleading names. They aren't blockchain "layers". They refer to replication.

L1 = databases replicated by multiple parties through a consensus protocol.

L2 = databases replicated by single parties.

E.g. w/e L2 Uniswap V3 runs on will be centralized.

L1 & L2 are misleading names. They aren't blockchain "layers". They refer to replication.

L1 = databases replicated by multiple parties through a consensus protocol.

L2 = databases replicated by single parties.

L1 & L2 are misleading names. They aren't blockchain "layers". They refer to replication.

L1 = databases replicated by multiple parties through a consensus protocol.

L2 = databases replicated by single parties.

E.g. w/e L2 Uniswap V3 runs on will be centralized.
